dji.sdk.api.Camera

Class DJICameraSystemState

  • java.lang.Object
    • dji.sdk.api.Camera.DJICameraSystemState

  • public class DJICameraSystemState
extends java.lang.Object

    Camera System State Class

    This class is a data structure for DJI camera system state. This data structure will be used in the callback of DJICameraSystemStateCallBack. Once the SDK receives state information from drone. It will invoke the callback and send the object of DJICameraS ystemState to the APP.
    Version:
    V2.4.0
    Author:
    DJI Software

      • isTakingRawPhoto

        public boolean isTakingRawPhoto
        Whether the camera is currently taking a RAW picture. If the camera is currently taking a RAW picture, isTakingRawPicture and isTakingSinglePicture will both return true.

      • isTakingContinusPhoto

        public boolean isTakingContinusPhoto
        Whether the camera is currently taking continuous pictures at the same interval. For example, if the interval is set to 1 second, the camera will take a picture every 1 second.

        Whether the camera is currently taking multiple pictures.

      • isUSBMode

        public boolean isUSBMode
        Support for Phantom 2 Vision+. Whether or not the camera is currently in USB mode. In order to sync photos from the application to your computer, the value of this property has to be true. Property only supported for the Phantom 2 Vision+.
